Install Docker Desktop
======================
Refer "https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/"

download and run "Docker Desktop Installer" 

Install Kubectl
===============
👉Install kubectl (if not already):

curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/windows/amd64/kubectl.exe"
mv kubectl.exe /c/Users/myuser/bin/
export PATH=$PATH:/c/Users/myuser/bin

kubectl version --client

Install Kind
============
Refer "https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/docs/user/quick-start/"

curl -Lo kind-windows-amd64.exe https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.31.0/kind-windows-amd64

Move-Item .\kind-windows-amd64.exe c:\some-dir-in-your-PATH\kind.exe
mv kind-windows-amd64.exe /c/Users/myuser/bin/

Create cluster with single node
kind create cluster --name my-2

check cluster list
kind get clusters

check docker running container
docker ps

To create multi node cluster
vi multicluster.yaml
kind: Cluster
apiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4
nodes:
- role: control-plane
- role: worker
- role: worker

kind create cluster --name my-2 --config=multicluster.yaml
To check currently you are interacting with which cluster(when you have multi node cluster)
kubectl config current-context

if you want to jump from one cluster to another
kubectl config get-contexts
kubectl config use-context <cluster-name>
kubectl config use-context kind-mycluster-app

get cluster info
kubectl cluster-info --context kind-<cluster-name>
or
kubectl cluster-info

To delete cluster
kind delete cluster --name <clustername>
